sentence: Wednesday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 6,393.31.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.87 billion.
Advancers stocks led declining by 1.28 to 1 ratio.
There were 1654 advancers and 1294 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 55 stocks reached a 52 week high and 17 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up .31% for the day; a total of 18.4 points.
Mattel, Inc. ( MAT ) had the largest percent change down (-3.21%) while Viacom Inc. ( VIAB ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.88%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .25% for the day; a total of 54.33 points.
United Technologies Corporation ( UTX ) had the largest percent change down (-1.44%) while Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.37%.
